Confluence uses its own wiki markup style, which is different from GitHub-flavored Markdown. Here's how your guide would look in Confluence's markup:

---

h2. 🛠 Setting up Environment with Terragrunt and Helm

h3. 📋 Prerequisites:
* Ensure Terraform is installed.
* Install [Terragrunt|https://terragrunt.gruntwork.io/docs/getting-started/install/].
* Install [Helm|https://helm.sh/docs/intro/install/].
* Ensure `kubectl` is installed.

h3. 📁 1. Copy Directory Structure and Update Region:

Assuming you have an existing directory structure for your Terragrunt configuration:
{code}
# 1.1: Copy the directory
cp -R original_env_directory new_env_directory

# 1.2: Navigate to the new directory
cd new_env_directory

# 1.3: Update the region in the appropriate Terragrunt or Terraform files
sed -i 's/us-west-1/us-east-1/g' **/*.tf
{code}

h3. ⚙️ 2. Terragrunt Apply:

To apply all your configurations with Terragrunt:
{code}
# 2.1: Navigate to the root of your Terragrunt configurations
cd path_to_terragrunt_configs

# 2.2: Run terragrunt to apply all
terragrunt run-all apply
{code}

h3. 🛡 3. Create Kubernetes Namespaces:

{code}
# 3.1: Create the 'infra' namespace
kubectl create namespace infra

# 3.2: Create the 'dev' namespace
kubectl create namespace dev
{code}

h3. 🚀 4. Install Helm Charts:

Ensure your kubeconfig points to the right Kubernetes cluster.
{code}
# 4.1: Add your Helm repo (replace 'your_repo_url' with the actual URL)
helm repo add your_repo_name your_repo_url

# 4.2: Update Helm repos
helm repo update

# 4.3: Install the 'infra' helm chart to the 'infra' namespace
helm install infra-helm-release your_repo_name/chart_name --version version_number --namespace infra

# 4.4: Install the 'dev' helm chart to the 'dev' namespace
helm install dev-helm-release your_repo_name/chart_name --version version_number --namespace dev
{code}

---

Please note that while Confluence supports the wiki markup, in newer versions, they have an editor that supports rich text and direct pasting of content. If you're using an older version or prefer the wiki markup, the above content should serve your purpose. If not, you might need to adapt the content in the Confluence editor.
